<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#123#000055#    525.18#">Va. Code Ann. § 55-525.18</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_55-525.18"/><heading><desig>§ 55-525.18.</desig><title>Scope of chapter; lay real estate settlement agents</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Except as provided in subsection B, this chapter applies only to transactions involving the purchase of or lending on the security of real estate located in the Commonwealth containing not more than four residential dwelling units.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Notwithstanding any rule of court or other provision of this chapter to the contrary:</p></bodyText><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b_1"/><heading><desig>1.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A lay real estate settlement agent may provide escrow, closing, and settlement services for any real property located within the Commonwealth, and receive compensation for such services, provided he is registered pursuant to and is in compliance with the provisions of this chapter with the exception of subsection A; and</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b_2"/><heading><desig>2.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A party to a real estate transaction involving the purchase of or lending on the security of real estate located in the Commonwealth containing more than four residential dwelling units shall have the same authority as a party to a real estate transaction as is provided pursuant to subsection B of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 55-525.19"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 55 -525.19">§ 55-525.19.<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000055#    525.19#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation></p></bodyText></level></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="1997 VA CH 716"><content><span normalizedCite="1997 Va. Ch. 716">1997, c. 716<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1997#000716#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, § 6.1-2.19; <citation normalizedCite="1998 VA CH 69"><content><span normalizedCite="1998 Va. Ch. 69">1998, cc. 69<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1998#000069#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1998 VA CH 162"><content><span normalizedCite="1998 Va. Ch. 162">162<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1998#000162#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1998 VA CH 736"><content><span normalizedCite="1998 Va. Ch. 736">736<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1998#000736#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1999 VA CH 647"><content><span normalizedCite="1999 Va. Ch. 647">1999, c. 647<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1999#000647#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, § 6.1-2.32; <citation normalizedCite="2010 VA CH 794"><content><span normalizedCite="2010 Va. Ch. 794">2010, c. 794<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2010#000794#"/